  "text": "According to literature the most consistently reported area of cingulate cortex to painful stimuli is the dorsal ACC or anterior middle cingulate cortex (aMCC). The activation of this area is one of the earliest responses to pain as this region has an impact in cortical nociception [CITATION_1] . A recent meta-analysis showed a significant likelihood of activation to painful stimuli in this brain area in healthy subjects [CITATION_2] . In case of our study we did not find any activation of this area, however, we have not used any painful stimuli during the scanning sessions and we investigated the difference between migraine patients and healthy controls.",
